was founded in by Samuel Curtis to manufacture fancy combs and buttons on the same property in Sandy Hook, Connecticut that we occupy In , Sam Curtis acquired sole interest in the business and later was joined by his son, Henry Gould The delicate buttons and combs needed to ship in special rigid Henry Curtis found it more efficient to construct the boxes on In the late Century, Curtis & Son began manufacturing rigid As the fancy buttons and combs went out of fashion, the packaging business During the early , Sam’s grandson William emphasized the production of By , Curtis exclusively concentrated on designing, printing, and converting folding In William’s son Nelson assumed the presidency, launching an era in which Curtis emerged as an innovative leader in custom Nelson Curtis sold the business to five of its executives in At the end of the the five owners started to contemplate Don Droppo was a Partner at Curtis’ trusted accounting firm, Peat In , Don acquired Curtis Packaging and immediately implemented new technologies to automate its workflow and keep Sam Curtis’ vision on In , Curtis Packaging became a family business yet Don Droppo, joined the company as Vice packaging company in North America to use % wind power, be % carbon neutral, and to be certified by the Forest Stewardships Council and the Sustainable Forestry In January , Don Droppo, , moved to a Patients who suffer a cardiac arrest must receive the highest quality CPR possible, which is known to be the cornerstone for survival however, certain studies show CPR skills can decay within three to six months following this Centura Health, the region’s health care leader, recognizes the importance of CPR competence, performance and delivery in saving more That’s why the Resuscitation Quality Improvement® program (RQI®), by the American Heart Association and Laerdal Medical and delivered by RQI Partners, is being implemented to help the hospital’s clinical staff achieve sustained mastery of CPR skills and competence, resulting in improved patient Centura Health is the first healthcare system in Colorado to adopt and implement RQI , an enhanced resuscitation quality improvement portfolio that was introduced in . RQI simulation stations will be placed throughout Centura Health’s hospitals, which will provide convenient access for healthcare professionals who participate in the The RQI program was launched in early July, enrolling more than ,000 “Providing top quality, whole person care is at the heart of what we do at Whether it is an advancement in training, technology or technique, if we can improve patient outcomes, we embrace it,” explained Rachel Miles, Vice President of Nursing Operations for Centura “We are steadfast in our commitment to reduce variation in care and improve clinical outcomes in our communities across Colorado and western We are excited to add the RQI program to our learning management ” Introduced in , the RQI program was designed for healthcare professionals with responsibility for patient Now, RQI prepares all healthcare system staff members to deliver CPR and verify competence in Basic Life Support, Advanced Life Support and Pediatric Advanced Life Support through simulated skills sessions and eLearning The program provides a platform for , mastery learning and performance, which is implemented through “low-dose, ” CPR quality improvement sessions, in minutes every days, that measure and verify competence each The program also provides analytics that can measure individual, department, facility or system To provide a complete solution to Centura Health, a brand new offering – RQI Responder – is now available for use by healthcare staff who are not directly involved in patient The addition of RQI Responder will ensure that every hospital employee, clinical and , is prepared to respond to a cardiac arrest event and able to provide “We are excited Centura Health is implementing the RQI program and working with the American Heart Association and Laerdal Medical to shift to a new standard of resuscitation care – verified competence,” said Naomi Amaha Gollnick, vice president of Health Strategies at the American Heart “This illustrates the staff’s commitment to making CPR a priority and furthering our mission to improve patient care and help save more ” To learn more about the RQI program and the value it brings to
